**Threats:**
- LLM API key exposure (HIGH) — API key must be in env var, never hardcoded
- LLM prompt injection through user-submitted code included in prompts (HIGH) — must sanitize input
- Unbounded batch processing consuming all DB resources (MEDIUM)
- Cross-tenant data in batch queries (HIGH)
**Mitigations:**
- LLM API key loaded from `AI_API_KEY` env var, required at startup if batch enabled
- User code in LLM prompts truncated to 500 chars, stripped of control characters
- Batch processes organizations sequentially, with configurable batch size
- All queries filter by organization_id
**Block on:** HIGH — LLM API key exposure and prompt injection
</threat_model>

